description: How should I structure components in this component library ?
globs: packages/components/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

- Each component should be in its own directory (e.g. packages/components/card)
- Each prop type should be in the same file as the component. Adding to that, prop types should be directly above the component.
- There should be no default export, always use named exports. The exports should be the components and the prop types for them.

```tsx
// Main component
// Can provide context for it s children to use or anything else.
type MyComponentProps = {
  children: React.ReactNode;
};
const MyComponent = (props: MyComponentProps) => {
  return <div>{props.children}</div>;
};

// Trigger component
// Can be used to trigger the content.
type MyComponentTriggerProps = {
  children: React.ReactNode;
};
const MyComponentTrigger = (props: MyComponentTriggerProps) => {
  return <div>{props.children}</div>;
};

// Content component
// Can be used to display the content.
type MyComponentContentProps = {
  children: React.ReactNode;
};
const MyComponentContent = (props: MyComponentContentProps) => {
  return <div>{props.children}</div>;
};

export {
  MyComponent,
  MyComponentTrigger,
  MyComponentContent,
  //
  MyComponentProps,
  MyComponentTriggerProps,
  MyComponentContentProps,
};
```
